						<summary>

						

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Achyutarāya Year: Śaka 1459, <hi rend="italic">Hemaḷambi, Kārttīka</hi>, ba. di. 12, <hi rend="italic">(utthāna-dvādaśi).</hi> Monday = 15th October 1537 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The latter portion of the record is damaged and the details are not clear. However, it registers a grant of the village Kāḷepalli renamed as Achyutēndramahārāyapura, for the services of lord Vīrēśvara of Lēpākshi. The donor was the son of Nandi Lakki-seṭṭi and Muddamāmbā. The stone charter was, it is stated, a copy of the copper-plate record.</p>						

						</summary>
